                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>5</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="448571" author="adilger" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 07:31:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33104&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33104&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11329&quot; title=&quot;add get_maintainer.pl script from kernel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11329&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11329&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: add get_maintainer.pl script&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) added the ability to find maintainers.  It is out of LU scope to notify them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="165590" author="adilger" created="Sat, 10 Sep 2016 08:11:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The upstream kernel has a &lt;tt&gt;get_maintainer.pl&lt;/tt&gt; script that looks in the MAINTAINERS file and automatically extracts the email addresses of the maintainers based on the &quot;F:&quot; label(s) for each subsystem.  It wouldn&apos;t be terrible if we used the same mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98597" author="rhenwood" created="Thu, 6 Nov 2014 20:52:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One suggestion for specifying &apos;areas of specific interest&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Matching regular expressions with inclusions - and exclusions. e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;andreas.dilger@intel.com: libcfs/* !lnet/* lustre/* !lustre/llite/vvp* !lustre/llite/lcommon* !lustre/lov/lovsub*
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
